ce:section.ce:para:
To assess the selectivity of the proposed method, the effect of several metal ions (Cu2+, Al3+, Zn2+, Ca2+, Mg2+, Ni+, Co2+, Pb2+, Cd2+, Hg2+, Li+, Sn2+, Na+ and K+) in two levels of concentration (10−4 and 10−6
                        M) on emission intensity of CDs were investigated. A significant quenching effect compared to other ions was observed for Fe(III) ions, indicating CDs could potentially be used for the detection of Fe(III) ions with high sensitivity (Fig. 7
                        ).
